ckground: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">187</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":187,\"repo\":\"danielberkompas/number\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Number is a pretentiously-named Elixir library which provides functions to convert numbers into a variety of different formats.</li>","updatedAt":"2015-06-28T11:33:58.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"h4cc/awesome-elixir","categoryHTML":"<h2>Reading</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/jwhiteman/a-little-elixir-goes-a-long-way\">The Little Schemer in Elixir</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/jwhiteman/a-little-elixir-goes-a-long-way\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">339</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":339,\"repo\":\"jwhiteman/a-little-elixir-goes-a-long-way\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Exercises and algorithms from the Little Schemer book, ported to Elixir.</li>","updatedAt":"2015-06-28T11:24:32.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"DataDaoDe/awesome-foss-apps","categoryHTML":"<h2>Web Apps (frontend only)</h2><h3><a href=\"https://github.com/travis-ci\">Travis CI</a></h3>","itemHTML":"<li>ruby, rails, sinatra, rabbitmq, ember</li>","updatedAt":"2015-06-28T09:47:55.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"DataDaoDe/awesome-foss-apps","categoryHTML":"<h2>Web Apps (frontend only)</h2><h3><a href=\"https://github.com/travis-ci\">Travis CI</a></h3>","itemHTML":"<li>MIT License</li>","updatedAt":"2015-06-28T09:47:55.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"owainlewis/awesome-artificial-intelligence","categoryHTML":"<h2>Courses</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.class-central.com/mooc/319/udacity-artificial-intelligence-for-robotics\">Artificial Intelligence For Robotics</a> - This class will teach you basic methods in Artificial Intelligence, including: probabilistic inference, planning and search, localization, tracking and control, all with a focus on robotics</li>","updatedAt":"2015-06-28T08:47:11.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"owainlewis/awesome-artificial-intelligence","categoryHTML":"<h2>Courses</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/1558601910\">Paradigms Of Artificial Intelligence Programming: Case Studies in Common Lisp</a> - Paradigms of AI Programming is the first text to teach advanced Common Lisp techniques in the context of building major AI systems</li>","updatedAt":"2015-06-28T08:47:11.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"owainlewis/awesome-artificial-intelligence","categoryHTML":"<h2>Courses</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/Cambridge-Handbook-Artificial-Intelligence/dp/0521691915\">The Cambridge Handbook Of Artificial Intelligence</a> - Written for non-specialists, it covers the discipline's foundations, major theories, and principal research areas, plus related topics such as artificial life</li>","updatedAt":"2015-06-28T08:47:11.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"owainlewis/awesome-artificial-intelligence","categoryHTML":"<h2>Courses</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/How-Create-Mind-Thought-Revealed/dp/0143124048/ref=pd_sim_14_3?ie=UTF8&#x26;refRID=0QY72H7NGRYH79R7S3K7\">How To Create A Mind</a> - Kurzweil discusses how the brain works, how the mind emerges, brain-computer interfaces, and the implications of vastly increasing the powers of our intelligence to address the world’s problems</li>","updatedAt":"2015-06-28T08:47:11.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"owainlewis/awesome-artificial-intelligence","categoryHTML":"<h2>Programming</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/Programming-Artificial-Intelligence-International-Computer/dp/0321417461\">Prolog Programming For Artificial Intelligence</a> - This best-selling guide to Prolog and Artificial Intelligence concentrates on the art of using the basic mechanisms of Prolog to solve interesting AI problems.</li>","updatedAt":"2015-06-28T08:47:11.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"owainlewis/awesome-artificial-intelligence","categoryHTML":"<h2>Philosophy</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.audible.co.uk/pd/Non-fiction/Our-Final-Invention-Audiobook/B00KLJMDH8\">Our Final Invention: Artificial Intelligence And The End Of The Human Era</a> - Our Final Invention explores the perils of the heedless pursuit of advanced AI. Until now, human intelligence has had no rival. Can we coexist with beings whose intelligence dwarfs our own? And will they allow us to?</li>","updatedAt":"2015-06-28T08:47:11.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"owainlewis/awesome-artificial-intelligence","categoryHTML":"<h2>Free Content</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://artint.info/html/ArtInt.html\">Foundations Of Computational Agents</a> - This book is published by Cambridge University Press, 2010</li>","updatedAt":"2015-06-28T08:47:11.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"owainlewis/awesome-artificial-intelligence","categoryHTML":"<h2>Free Content</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://ai.stanford.edu/~nilsson/QAI/qai.pdf\">The Quest For Artificial Intelligence</a> - This book traces the history of the subject, from the early dreams of eighteenth-century (and earlier) pioneers to the more successful work of today's AI engineers.</li>","updatedAt":"2015-06-28T08:47:11.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"owainlewis/awesome-artificial-intelligence","categoryHTML":"<h2>Videos</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sc-KbuZqGkI\">The Unreasonable Effectiveness Of Deep Learning</a> - The Director of Facebook's AI Research, Dr. Yann LeCun gives a talk on deep convolutional neural networks and their applications to machine learning and computer vision</li>","updatedAt":"2015-06-28T08:47:11.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"owainlewis/awesome-artificial-intelligence","categoryHTML":"<h2>Learning</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://research.microsoft.com/pubs/209355/DeepLearning-NowPublishing-Vol7-SIG-039.pdf\">Deep Learning. Methods And Applications</a> Free book from Microsoft Research</li>","updatedAt":"2015-06-28T08:47:11.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"owainlewis/awesome-artificial-intelligence","categoryHTML":"<h2>Learning</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://neuralnetworksanddeeplearning.com\">Neural Networks And Deep Learning</a> - Neural networks and deep learning currently provide the best solutions to many problems in image recognition, speech recognition, and natural language processing. This book will teach you the core concepts behind neural networks and deep learning</li>","updatedAt":"2015-06-28T08:47:11.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"owainlewis/awesome-artificial-intelligence","categoryHTML":"<h2>Courses</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/Jeff-Hawkins/e/B001KHNZ7C/ref=sr_ntt_srch_lnk_11?qid=1435480927&#x26;sr=8-11\">On Intelligence</a> - Hawkins develops a powerful theory of how the human brain works, explaining why computers are not intelligent and how, based on this new theory, we can finally build intelligent machines. Also audio version available from audible.com</li>","updatedAt":"2015-06-28T08:43:29.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"afonsopacifer/awesome-flexbox","categoryHTML":"<h2>Who to Follow</h2>","itemHTML":"<li>Afonso Pacifer <a href=\"https://twitter.com/afonsopacifer\">@afonsopacifer</a></li>","updatedAt":"2015-06-28T00:41:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"afonsopacifer/awesome-flexbox","categoryHTML":"<h2>Who to Follow</h2>","itemHTML":"<li>Rachel Andrew <a href=\"https://twitter.com/rachelandrew\">@rachelandrew</a></li>","updatedAt":"2015-06-28T00:41:02.000Z"}]}},"pageContext":{"type":"day","from":1435449600000,"to":1435535999999,"previousId":"2015-06-29","nextId":"2015-06-27","nextName":"Jun 27th, 2015","previousName":"Jun 29th, 2015"}},"staticQueryHashes":["228695001","2744905544","4035379035"]}